This file contains the data about the Loewy structure
of Singer algebras A[q,z] with 3501 <= z <= 4000.
The contents is a list of length three,
the first entry being this description,
the second entry being the array [3501,4000] of the smallest and largest
value of z in question,
and the third being the lexicographically sorted
list of entries of the form '[ z, q, n, m, l, v', d, dec, delta ]',
which belongs to the algebra A = A[q,z].
The number n is defined as the multiplicative order of q modulo z.
With e = (q^n-1)/z, we have m = m(q,e) and l = LL( A ).
The Loewy vector v = [ v_1, v_2, ... ] of A is defined by
where J is the Jacobson radical of A; the length of v is l.
We encode v by a vector v' where subsequent equal entries i with
multiplicity j > 1 are abbreviated as [ i, j ];
thus v' = [ [ 1, j ] ] stands for v = [ 1, 1, ..., 1 ] of length j.
Set q' = q mod m; a decomposition (x_1 ... x_n)^{q'-1} =
of length N = l-1-n(q-q')/m is encoded by d = [ k_1, k_2, ..., k_N ],
where e k_i = \sum_{j=1}^n a_{i,j} q^{j-1} holds;
if no such decomposition is known then d = 0 is stored.
The flag dec is 0 if (x_1 ... x_n)^{q'-1} can be written as a product
of monomials of degree m plus perhaps one more monomial,
and 1 otherwise.
Finally, delta = \lfloor n (q-1)/m \rfloor + 1 - l.
For each z, there is an entry for each q with 2 <= q <= z+1
that is coprime to z and such that q is minimal in the cyclic subgroup
of prime residues modulo z generated by q.
